cs.ET, cs.IT, cs.AR, cs.SI, cs.LG

The paper deals with the design of ADCs that maximize the information in the converted signal by frequency shaping the quantization noise. This involves techniques from information theory (cs.IT) and signal processing (cs.AR), as well as optimization and control theory (cs.ET). The paper also discusses the application of these techniques to wireline and wireless channels (cs.SI), and presents experimental results (cs.LG).
